A 1 kilometer radius is a distance of 1,000 meters. A kilometer is a little longer than half a mile, or about 0.62 miles. It takes about 10 to 12 minutes to walk one kilometer at a moderate pace.
Some examples of things that are about one kilometer in length include:
The distance around a small pond
The length of a neighborhood street
A soccer field
The Statue of Liberty
An Olympic-size pool
A basketball court
